author: NEW YORK DAILY NEWS
title: Odell Beckham Jr. 'coming along' but won't practice Friday
text:
Alex Goodlett/Getty Images Odell Beckham Jr. is having a solid season for the Giants, catching 31 balls for 428 yards and three TDs. Giants wide receiver Odell Beckham Jr. (hamstring) will not practice Friday, but Tom Coughlin has not ruled him out for Monday's game against the Eagles.
If Beckham shows enough improvement for Sunday's practice, he could be on the field. Coughlin also said Beckham doesn't necessarily have to practice Sunday in order to play Monday.
"He's coming along," Coughlin said.
